# Li source conventions

**Unproved code does not compile.** No exceptions in user modules.

## Every function: `def` (not `proc`)

```nim
def f(x: int) -> int
  requires x > 0
  ensures result > 0
  decreases x
=
  ...
```

Bare `proc` is rejected. Use **`extern proc`** only for FFI stubs.

## Forbidden

`Any`, `unsafe`, `safe`, `verified`, `sorry`, `assume`, bare `cast[T](e)`

## Allowed casts

`cast[T](e, proof)` only.

## Loops

`while` must have `invariant` and `decreases`.

## Indices

Use refinements `{i: int | 0 <= i and i < N}` or proof-carrying index types — not raw `int` for grid access without proof.

## IO

User code proves against axioms in `trusted.lean`; game/sim `step` procs are total; driver loop is trusted `IO`.

## Parallelism (v1)

`parallel for` on **shared memory** (OpenMP). Safety = proved disjoint writes + `Send`/`Sync`. Run `scripts/test_race_reject.sh` — exploit fixtures must fail compile.

No unchecked overflow. `int` + `float` mixing requires explicit proved conversion.
